        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-14 14:52:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Pamela, I think in the short term while OOM has to continue forking ONAP application config files the best way would be to include OOM contributors on changes to the \"policy/docker\" gerrit project.  That way we know that we have to resync.  Typically, all we need to tweak in each file is a hostname or IP address to align with the internal kubernetes services we are using.  Typically, we would mount individual files, but in this case we mounted the entire directory and as a result we needed to include all the files even though there were no changes to them.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
